defs.docs:
A single-threaded executor which executes tasks on the same thread from which
 they are spawned.

defs.name: CurrentThread
defs.docs: Executes tasks on the current thread

defs.name: TaskExecutor
defs.docs: Executes futures on the current thread.

defs.name: Turn
defs.docs: Returned by the `turn` function.

defs.name: has_polled
defs.docs: `true` if any futures were polled at all and `false` otherwise.

defs.name: Entered
defs.docs: A `CurrentThread` instance bound to a supplied execution context.

defs.name: RunError
defs.docs: Error returned by the `run` function.

defs.name: RunTimeoutError
defs.docs: Error returned by the `run_timeout` function.

defs.name: TurnError
defs.docs: Error returned by the `turn` function.

defs.name: BlockError
defs.docs: Error returned by the `block_on` function.

defs.name: block_on_all
defs.docs: Run the executor bootstrapping the execution with the provided future.

defs.name: spawn
defs.docs: Executes a future on the current thread.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new instance of `CurrentThread`.

defs.name: new_with_park
defs.docs:
Create a new instance of `CurrentThread` backed by the given park
 handle.

defs.name: is_idle
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the executor is currently idle.

defs.name: spawn
defs.docs: Spawn the future on the executor.

defs.name: block_on
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, future: F) -> Result<F::Item, BlockError<F::Error>>
defs.docs: Synchronously waits for the provided `future` to complete.

defs.name: run
defs.docs:
Run the executor to completion, blocking the thread until **all**
 spawned futures have completed.

defs.name: run_timeout
defs.value: fn (&mut self, duration: Duration) -> Result<(), RunTimeoutError>
defs.docs:
Run the executor to completion, blocking the thread until all
 spawned futures have completed **or** `duration` time has elapsed.

defs.name: turn
defs.value: fn (&mut self, duration: Option<Duration>) -> Result<Turn, TurnError>
defs.docs: Perform a single iteration of the event loop.
